//tutorial link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YXfA5O5Mr18

on Mac:
brew install podman
//containers are a Linux technology, the only way to run containers on other platforms is to rely on a Limux virtual machine, podman on MacOS and Windows requires a virtual machine. 
//the default machine name os podman-machine-default if a machine name is not specified as an argument, then podman-machine-default will be started.
//only one podman virtual machine can be started, if a virtual machine is already running, podman machine start returns an error.
podman machine init
podman machine start    
podman info
podman version
